</style></head><body style=" font-family:'Cantarell'; font-size:10pt; font-weight:400; font-style:normal;">
<ul style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; -qt-list-indent: 1;"><li style=" margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;">Someone cannot claim to have fellowship with God if they are constantly and unrepentantly walking in darkness because if they were walking with God, the light would drown out the evil practices and cause sanctification.</li>
<li style=" margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;">This doesn't mean slip ups or repentant relapses into sin, but it means trying to talk yourself into thinking the sinful actions are okay, or even ignoring that it is sinful to begin with.</li>
<li style=" margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;">God's grace and light extend to those who repent and accept it (metanoia). Unrepentant hearts are not walking with God.</li></ul></body></html>